<br>
EQ is a melee based game. The game revolves around the Warrior. In order to make yourself more useful, you MUST be able to assist them. You must have utility. Who cares if we evac? Druids do it as well and they have utility to heal, buff, regen, blah, blah, balh. <br>
<br>
Yes, AOE groups are neato, we rule. I have lived most of my pathetic wizard life Aoe'ing. But do we do it well without help, like jboots, no. Do you get your epic by quad kiting, no.  But be honest, the best, most challenging things in the game are in Dungeons, period. Where are AOE groups there, unless there is a pathing problem?<br>
<br>
Lures are a slap in the face. They do nothing than make us less efficient casters, reducing our utility. GREAT! I can hit mobs with my lures, after 2k of damage is dealt, I am oom. Plus, I have been summoned 5 times.<br>
<br>
We have broken spell lines, like Al'Kabor, Fade, Eye, Pet, the list goes on and on. And what does VI do to fix it? Nothing. <br>
<br>
What do Wizards do to fix them? Nothing. We sit around and nit pick about how these spells have a use in the most limited of situations. <br>
<br>
I have said it before, and I will say it again, this game is all about efficiency. Why bother doing a lame quest for a crappy pet? Don't waste your time. You know how many Wizards I see having pets? Fookin ZERO. Why? Becasue it isn't worth their time. Why would a guild give a crap about helping you with your epic when cleric's are much more useful. Correct me if I am wrong, but Our Epic is self only. How shitty is that? <br>
<br>
What do we do better than anyone else, without a shadow of a doubt? NOTHING. What utility do we have? Hmmm, lemme think. We can invis folks, one by one. We can cast a 5 pt stackable damage shield, we can evac. We can cast see invis. We can snare (AE). I am not saying we need utility, but for the love of HESUS, make us group friendly! Hell, make concussion cast instantly and be unresistable or freakin something. SOMETHING!<br>
<br>
Hell, I could go on and on, being flame bait, but bottom line is that Wizards are the bottom of the barrel in any situation except when folks need a ride, and even then, if they need a sow, they're going to a Druid.<br>
<br>
You know what? I know people will include miniscule things we can do  just because that's the way Wizards play. We fight for scraps. I wish we could just come together in protest, but we won't. Why do you all keep taking this crap? Mainly, because we are greedy and hooked on EQ.<br>
<br>
I feel like I have wasted my time as a Wizard. I feel like we, as Wizards keep letting VI slap us in the face with lame ass things like Bane spells, that you have to quest for (not worth it, again), that only 1 fookin level in the game can use. They make us numb by giving lures, I hate lures. It just shows our ineptitude. Our damage does not go up signifigantly from 51 to 59.  Our pluses do not weigh up to our minuses, PERIOD, DOT!<br>
<br>
Until we all come to some sort of agreement, status quo will remain constant. Our spells will remain broken and we will continue to increase posts on Graffe's OOM Forum. Try finding another class who has a thread for retiring folks.<br>
<br>
/e awaits flaming, <br>
<br>
Soliceia...more to come.....Sorry Grimstaff, the spellcheck macro is broken, and I have to go, I hope there are not too many typos. I want to type sooooo much more, I hope people would just listen.<br>
 <p>Knowledge is power, so to be unknown is to be invunerable.</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uoglzogl.showPublicProfile?language=EN>oglzogl</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/26/01 7:08:40 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.toddpowelson.com/selfish.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Read and Flame.</span><hr size=1> So what do you propose? What can we possibly do?<br>
I am experiencing the same thing you are. I sign on for a few hours a week anymore and become so discusted that my EQ jones is cured for a while. Then I log off and do something else. I really like this game and will not delete my account, really just because I want to see what happens with the game. Maybe, down the road, in an alternate reality, things will get better and I could become a full time EQ freak again. As it stands now, EQ is called &quot;Ever-bad-taste-in-my-mouth&quot;.<br>
The only way that I ever see this game changing is if all the INT casters (because we all have problems. Except maybe enchanters) create a mele and use it as our primary. How likely is that? But I am sure if that happened (everybody played mele) VI might want the caster classes to look more attractive. I personally will not develop another character on EQ because my wizard is my first and my main and what I wanted to play in the first place. There is no way that I am spending the time developing another class only to find out it sucks too (even though I have a low level shaman and monk I enjoy I will never get them up to the level of my wizard).<br>
When VI closed down their message boards without addressing any issues raised and then changed our class description, I realized that the players are powerless and unheard. Even if they do not agree with the problems raised by players, I just cannot stand the way they treat us... it is just dead air. Talking to VI is like talking to a wall. This is what I mean when I say &quot;what can we, as players, do?&quot; I hope they they are listening to Graffe and maybe other wizards ideas but VI has done nothing to make me really believe it will get better. Still, I hope. I have had fun I admit, and I hope I will again.<br>
Well, anyways, I still enjoy coming here a few times a week to read the news and see what is happening. Thanks for being patient with me <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uxandollf.showPublicProfile?language=EN>xandollf</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/26/01 10:21:50 pm)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Read and Flame.</span><hr size=1> I was always told if ya dont have something nice to say, dont say anything at all. Well..<br>
