<br>
Warrior:<br>
1=1<br>
2=2.1<br>
3=3.3<br>
4=4.5<br>
5=5.9<br>
6=7<br>
<br>
Very straight forward, there's a bit of extra functionality to a melee class, where being able to balance things between them will help, but in general, it's linear.  Now, how I see the wizard class:<br>
<br>
1=0.9<br>
2=2.2<br>
3=3.9<br>
4=5.5<br>
5=6.9<br>
6=8.4<br>
<br>
The more wizards, the faster the mobs go down, to the point where they can't do much damage before they go down in a well coordinated group.  As always, uber-HP mobs in Velious reduce how useful 8 people are against a single mob since you can't burn the mobs down quickly enough, but in general, we gain more power in numbers as we work together.  It's just the weird way the game is designed that lets this happen, but in a 3 second period, 6 level 56 wizards casting draught will do 4008 damage in 3 seconds with no resists.  That can't be matched by six level 56 melees.  Even if the mob goes after one of the wizards, there's still five wizards left casting, so add 3340 damage to the mob, and if there are clerics around, that first wizard may still be up, so again, add 3340.  <br>
<br>
With the exception of the high high level zones where the mobs have 32k HP, you've just done 10680 damage in 12 seconds to a mob if there are no resists.  This doesn't even take 20 percent of the mana pool of the wizards either.  But, this power is to take things down quick, if a single wizards chaincasts a bar of mana, he/she still won't do near this ammount of damage because of agro.<br>
<br>
In spite of this power, in a single group situation with only one wizard, we still need some work, but we also have a VERY solid amount of power at level 55+.  Without too much effort, at 56 you should be able to cast 13 draughts on a full bar of mana.  That includes things like Carmine, but doesn't include most of the new Velious items.  So, show your power if you've made it to level 55, because you DO have a good amount, you just need to realize it.<br>
 <p>Targonis Manastorm<br>
