<br>
Waiting on VI to fix the class isn't very fun.  The changes come very slow and no ammount of yipping at them seems to help.  I've seen really good petitions with hundreds of player signatures be tossed out without so much as a line of explanation.  Hard to get excited when VI makes a promise to fix us...heh.  If you don't like the class, try another.  The secret is to have fun playing, so if you're not having fun, change something.  Change playstyle, class, even games, but have fun.  This is your hobby, you should enjoy it.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uoglzogl.showPublicProfile?language=EN>oglzogl</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/27/01 6:38:15 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.toddpowelson.com/selfish.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Read and Flame.</span><hr size=1> Point well taken Beryl. However, after 100+ days of doing something I am sure you understand that something is expected in return for your troubles. As it stands now I am just not sure what the return is. We were told we can expect to gain incredible power as we age which makes up for our weak start. My experience has taught me this simply is not true. And it isn't class envy or pet envy (Freud would have a field day with that term) but simply that I think the wizard class is broken (I don't think they are as broken as some people do. I do think they.. we.. are broken however). Maybe there are better wizards than me out there who dispute this.. big damn deal.<br>
I realize this really isn't the place to accomplish anything as far as changing the game goes but hey, this is a rant board after all. <br>
Sorry if I said too much Xandolf but I was always taught to speak my mind. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm4.showMessage?topicID=207.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm4.showMessage?topicID=224.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br></td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm4.emailToFriend?topicID=233.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm4.threadControl?topicID=233.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm4.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=233.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm4.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=233.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub23.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="graffeswizardcompilationfrm1">General Discussion<option value="graffeswizardcompilationfrm3">Trade Forum<option value="graffeswizardcompilationfrm4">Rant Forum<option value="graffeswizardcompilationfrm8">Mob Dropped Spells<option value="graffeswizardcompilationfrm10">Class Balance & Class Bugs<option value="graffeswizardcompilationfrm22">Out of Mana<option value="g